This paper discusses the use of algorithms in hiring, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the technical aspects of algorithmic assessments, including data collection and prediction targets, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the risks and trade-offs of algorithmic choices, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of algorithmic de-biasing techniques in relation to antidiscrimination law, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
